OL,3,C'Chronic' under-performance of boys at
OL,4,CGCSE should be treated as major issue
OL,6,FLast year, more than a fifth (21.8%)
OL,7,Fof UK GCSE entries were awarded the
OL,8,Ftop grades ` at least a 7 or an A
OL,9,Fgrade, down from 22.0% in 2023.
OL,11,FBut it remained higher than in 2019 `
OL,12,Fthe year before the pandemic ` when
OL,13,F20.8% of GCSE entries scored the top
OL,14,Fgrades.
OL,16,FThe proportion of total female entries
OL,17,Fawarded grade 7/A or above was 24.7%
OL,18,Flast year ` 5.7 percentage points
OL,19,Fhigher than total male entries (19.0%).
