OL,3,C'Chronic' under-performance of boys at
OL,4,CGCSE should be treated as major issue
OL,6,FWhile traditional A*-G grades are used
OL,7,Ffor GCSE in Northern Ireland and
OL,8,FWales, these have been replaced in
OL,9,FEngland with a 9-1 system, where 9 is
OL,10,Fthe highest.
OL,12,FA 4 is broadly equivalent to a C
OL,13,Fgrade, and a 7 is broadly equivalent
OL,14,Fto an A.
OL,16,FIn England, many students who do not
OL,17,Fsecure at least a grade 4 ` which is
OL,18,Fconsidered a "standard pass" ` in
OL,19,FEnglish and/or maths GCSE are required
OL,20,Fto retake the subjects during post-16
OL,21,Feducation.
